Spectogram, chroma.

Visualise music pitch in a spiral because higher = higher but also, octave is represented by the same angle on the spiral. 

Chromagram is in theory easier to read and understand than an spectogram. 

A cent is a 'maatstaaf' in pitch. Normal people can hear a pitch difference of about 25c, trained musicians can get that down to 10c. 

Er zijn verschillende chroma analyses:
- manhattan (sum of colom / the sum)
- Euclidean (root mean square)
- Chebyshev (maximum) 

IK ZIT ZO NIET OP TE LETTEN LEES GEWOON MAAR DIE FOKKING TEKSTEN WANT DIT SLAAT NERGENS OP. 


HULP COMMANDO's voor het vervormen van data:
- pivot_wide
